dataLineage.statement:
Layer was downloaded as a shapefile by ITOS from a Dropbox link provided by the IMO. It was then analyzed by ITOS for errors. Those errors were corrected and the layer was sent back to UNOCHA as a feature class within a file geodatabase.
The following errors were found and fixed by ITOS: 1. Non-essential fields 'Urban', 'Timestamp' 'Source', 'Source_1', 'Timestam_1', 'Source_12' and 'Timestam_2' were removed 2. Created and populated Admin0 name and p-code fields 3. Created and populated reference name field 4. Fixed nesting errors with Admin0-2. As instructed by IMO, Admin3's borders for Admin0-2 were matched to the government data. 5. Admin2 names and p-codes haveÂ been matched to Admin2 layer. 6. Created and populated Admin1 name and p-code fields. 7. New p-codes and AltNames have been provided by IMO for Admin3s in Yobe. They replaced the old p-codes and AltNames. 8. Admin3 p-code format has been changed. Previously, the Admin3 p-code portions began with the last digit of the Admin2 p-code. They were changed to a leading zero 9. Found and fixed 123 gap errors and 138 overlap errors. 10. Created and populated Senatorial District name and p-code fields.
DISCLAIMER: Dataset has Senatorial District attribution fields that are not standard for CODs but may be helpful for cartographic purposes. Admin p-codes do not include a Senatorial District p-code portion.
